c length is assigned to the base element. The characteristic length can be determined by users of the computer aided analysis, or be calculated using geometry of the base element. The characteristic length and the representative node collectively define a surface boundary that divides elements in the grid model into two groups. The first group contains potential neighbors, while the second group contains non-neighbors. Only elements in the first group are further processed using traditional procedures to determine whether each of them is indeed a neighbor element according to one of the neighborhood determination criteria.
